“Your gateway to your health record”
My Hakeem is a mobile application that enables its users to access and view their pre-booked medical appointments, also selective medical information such as; active and pending medications, recent immunizations, pending and complete laboratory tests, allergies, and vital signs that are stored on the user’s electronic health record registered within any healthcare facility that implements “Hakeem program”. It also enables the user to request the delivery of his/her monthly medication prescription refills. 
You can benefit from My Hakeem services from anywhere and at any time by downloading My Hakeem application or accessing My Hakeem platform myhakeem.jo
Users can access My Hakeem mobile application or MyHakeem.jo platform by using the same login credentials. 




”بوابتك لملفك الطبي الإلكتروني“
 حكيمي هو تطبيق إلكتروني للهواتف الذكية يمكن المستخدمين من الإطلاع على بعض المعلومات الصحية الموثقة في السجل الطبي الإلكتروني الخاص بهم مثل خاصية الاطلاع على المواعيد الطبية في عيادات الاختصاص في أي من المنشآت الصحية التي تطبق ”برنامج حكيم“، وخاصية الاطلاع على الأدوية الحالية، الحساسيات، المطاعيم، نتائج الفحوصات المخبرية والعلامات الحيوية للمستخدم. بالإضافة إلى خدمة طلب توصيل الأدوية المكررة شهريًا. 
يمكن الإستفادة من خدمات حكيمي في أي وقت ومن أي مكان من خلال الدخول إلى منصة حكيمي MyHakeem.jo  أو تطبيق الهواتف الذكية "حكيمي My Hakeem " باستخدام نفس إسم المستخدم (الرقم الوطني / رقم الملف الطبي) وكلمة المرور الخاصة بك.

يعد طبكان من أبرز الأنظمة الطبية على مستوى الشرق الأوسط في مجال الصحة الإلكترونية والسياحة العلاجية حيث أن مهمتنا الأساسية هي أن نقوم بتحسين حياة المرضى عن طريق اتاحة الوصول الى الرعاية الصحية الملائمة ذات الأسعار الجيدة والتي تتناسب مع قدرات المرضى .كما أن منصة تبادل المعلومات الطبية التي يوفرها طبكان تضمن تشخيصات طبية أكثر دقة وبالتالي اعطاء علاجات أكثر فعالية .
أن طبكان يعمل على توفير خدمات حقيقية وادوات فعالة عن طريق الإنترنت مثل خدمة العلاج عن بعد الى عدد كبير من المستخدمين المرضى والأطباء والمستشفيات و مراكز التشخيص والصيدليات و وكلاء الرعاية الصحية وغيرهم . اننا في طبكان نضع احتياجات المرضى ورضاهم كأولوية أولى حيث اننا وفرنا كافة الادوات والخدمات التي تضمن عملية علاجية سهلة ومنظمة. إنظم إلينا اليوم ولاحظ الفرق في جودة ونوعية الخدمات.

‘Dr@Hakeem’ is the first national mobile application that provides full details for the physicians pertaining to their daily appointments and patients’ medical history, in order to improve the healthcare process in the public health sector in Jordan.

‘Dr@Hakeem’ mobile application has been created to support the already existing cycle of the “Hakeem” program; the first national e-health initiative in Jordan to automate the public health sector, which was launched in October 2009 under the patronage of H.M. King Abdullah II. 

‘Dr@Hakeem’ app enables the physicians to track down their patients’ medical appointments remotely wherever they are and whenever they want to, it also provides full details about the patient’s medical history such as vital signs, allergies, health problems, laboratory tests, radiology reports and medications, in order to improve healthcare process.

The program aims to facilitate efficient high quality healthcare in Jordan through nationwide implementation of an electronic health record solution which enables the healthcare service providers to electronically access medical records of patients simply by entering the patient’s national ID number. 

‘Dr@Hakeem’ Application Features:
- Main clinics screen: Displays the main clinics available in the Hakeem system.
- Sub-clinics screen: Displays the sub clinics available in the Hakeem system.
- Appointments screen: Displays the patients’ scheduled appointments.
- Appointment details screen: Enables doctors to view the (Patient’s name, hospital/health care center name, clinic’s special instructions). 
- Patient information screen: Displays the patient’s basic information in addition to his vital signs and medical record.
- Patient health summery screen: Displays the patient’s health problems, allergies, medications, vaccines … etc.
- Laboratory tests details screen: Enables the doctor to view his patient’s laboratory orders and test results.
- Radiology screen: Enables the doctor to view his patient’s radiology reports.

The FreeStyle LibreLink app is approved for use with FreeStyle Libre and FreeStyle Libre 2 system sensors. You can check your glucose by scanning your sensor with your phone. Now FreeStyle Libre 2 system sensor users can get automatic glucose readings in the FreeStyle LibreLink app, updated every minute, and also receive alarms when your glucose is low or high. [1][2]

You can use the FreeStyle LibreLink app to:

* View your current glucose reading, trend arrow and glucose history
* Receive low or high glucose alarms with FreeStyle Libre 2 system sensors [2]
* Add notes to track your food, insulin use and exercise
* See reports, such as Time in Range and Daily Patterns
* Share your data with your doctor and family, with your permission [3]

SMARTPHONE COMPATIBILITY
Compatibility may vary between phones and operating systems. Learn more about compatible phones at http://FreeStyleLibre.com.

USING YOUR APP AND READER WITH THE SAME SENSOR
Alarms can only be issued on your FreeStyle Libre 2 reader or your phone (not both). To receive alarms on your phone, you must start the sensor with the app. To receive alarms on your FreeStyle Libre 2 reader, you must start the sensor with your reader. Once the sensor has been started with the reader, you can also scan that sensor with your phone.

Remember that the app and reader do not share data with each other. For complete information on a device, scan your sensor every eight hours with that device; otherwise, your reports will not include all your data. You can upload and view data from all of your devices on LibreView.com.

APP INFORMATION
FreeStyle LibreLink is intended for measuring glucose levels in people with diabetes when used with a sensor. For more information on how to use FreeStyle LibreLink, refer to the User’s Manual, which can be accessed through the app. If you require a printed User’s Manual, contact Abbott Diabetes Care Customer Support.

Consult a healthcare professional to confirm if this product is right for you or if you have questions about how to use this product to make treatment decisions.

Learn more at http://FreeStyleLibre.com.

[1] If you are using the FreeStyle LibreLink app, you must also have access to a blood glucose monitoring system, as the app does not provide one.  

[2] Alarms that you receive do not include your glucose reading, so you must scan your sensor to check your glucose.

[3] Use of FreeStyle LibreLink and LibreLinkUp requires registration with LibreView.

The sensor housing, FreeStyle, Libre, and related brand marks are marks of Abbott. Other trademarks are the property of their respective owners.

For additional legal notices and terms of use, go to http://FreeStyleLibre.com.

========

To resolve any technical or Customer Service issues that you are having with a FreeStyle Libre product, please contact FreeStyle Libre Customer Service directly.
